# Citation Tracking Standards

This document defines standards for reference management, DOI tracking, dataset citations, and code citations in research projects.

---

## Core Principle: Every External Input Has a Citation

Any data, code, algorithm, or idea that originates outside your project must be cited with sufficient detail for a reader to locate the original source.

---

## Reference Types

### Citation Categories

| Category | What to Cite | Format |
|----------|-------------|--------|
| Academic paper | Methods, algorithms, theoretical foundations | BibTeX / DOI |
| Dataset | Training data, evaluation benchmarks | DOI / URL + access date |
| Software | Libraries, frameworks, tools | Version + DOI (if available) |
| Code | Specific implementations, snippets | Repository URL + commit SHA |
| Pre-trained model | Foundation models, embeddings | Model card URL + version |
| Standard | ISO, RFC, WCAG | Standard number + version |

---

## DOI Tracking

### When DOIs Are Required

| Source | DOI Required? | Alternative |
|--------|--------------|-------------|
| Published paper | Yes | arXiv ID for preprints |
| Dataset (Zenodo, Figshare) | Yes | URL + access date + hash |
| Software (JOSS, SciPy) | Yes, if available | Version + URL |
| Blog post, tutorial | No | URL + access date + archive.org link |
| Internal document | No | File path + commit SHA |

### DOI Best Practices

- [ ] Every citation has a DOI when one exists
- [ ] DOIs are validated (resolve correctly) before publication
- [ ] DOIs use the `https://doi.org/` prefix format
- [ ] For software without DOI: use Zenodo to mint one from a GitHub release

---

## Dataset Citations

### Required Metadata

| Field | Example | Required? |
|-------|---------|-----------|
| Name | "ImageNet-1K" | Yes |
| Version / Date | "ILSVRC2012" / "2024-01-15 snapshot" | Yes |
| Creator | "Stanford Vision Lab" | Yes |
| DOI / URL | `https://doi.org/10.xxxx` | Yes |
| License | "CC BY 4.0" | Yes |
| Access date | "2026-02-01" | Yes (for URLs) |
| Hash (SHA-256) | `a1b2c3d4...` | Recommended |
| Size | "150 GB" | Recommended |
| Description | "1000-class image classification" | Recommended |

### Dataset Citation Format

```bibtex
@dataset{deng2009imagenet,
  author    = {Deng, Jia and Dong, Wei and Socher, Richard and Li, Li-Jia and Li, Kai and Fei-Fei, Li},
  title     = {ImageNet: A Large-Scale Hierarchical Image Database},
  year      = {2009},
  doi       = {10.1109/CVPR.2009.5206848},
  note      = {Version ILSVRC2012, accessed 2026-02-01, SHA-256: a1b2c3d4...}
}
```

### Dataset Versioning

- [ ] Dataset version is pinned (not "latest")
- [ ] If dataset is dynamic: snapshot date and hash are recorded
- [ ] Data preprocessing steps are cited if from another project
- [ ] Derived datasets cite their source datasets

---

## Software and Code Citations

### Library Citations

For every library that materially contributes to results:

```bibtex
@software{pytorch2024,
  author  = {PyTorch Contributors},
  title   = {PyTorch},
  version = {2.2.0},
  year    = {2024},
  url     = {https://pytorch.org},
  doi     = {10.5281/zenodo.XXXXXXX}
}
```

### When to Cite Software

| Usage | Cite? | Rationale |
|-------|-------|-----------|
| Core framework (PyTorch, TensorFlow) | Yes | Results depend on implementation |
| Statistical library (scipy, statsmodels) | Yes | Test implementations may differ |
| Utility (pandas, numpy) | Recommended | Version affects numerical behavior |
| Standard library (os, sys) | No | Universally available |
| Build tools (make, pip) | No | Not part of results |

### Code Repository Citations

For code adapted from another project:

```bibtex
@misc{smith2025implementation,
  author    = {Smith, J.},
  title     = {Efficient Transformer Implementation},
  year      = {2025},
  url       = {https://github.com/jsmith/efficient-transformer},
  note      = {Commit abc123, accessed 2026-02-01, MIT License}
}
```

- [ ] Repository URL is permanent (not a fork that may be deleted)
- [ ] Specific commit SHA is recorded (not just "main branch")
- [ ] License compatibility is verified
- [ ] Modifications from the original are documented

